Police in Delta State said its men have been combing the bushes in search of the state chairman of the Nigeria Labour Congress (NLC), Goodluck Ofobruku, as well as the gunmen who kidnapped him at the weekend. Police Commissioner Hafiz Inuwa confirmed the abduction, cautioning residents, particularly VIPs, to be careful about their movement. Ofobruku was abducted on Saturday from his official Sienna car on his street as he drove out to buy medicine. Ofonyeade said the kidnappers took the Labour chief into the bush, leaving his car where they abducted him.